<% content_for :section_title, "Configuration" %>

<p class="text-xl">Configuring Jumpstart Pro is easy. We've built a handy configuration wizard interface in development mode to save you time configuring your application.</p>

<%= h2_with_anchor "Credentials" %>
<p>Rails credentials are used for configuration API keys. Check out the <%= link_to "Credentials", credentials_docs_path, class: "text-primary-500 underline" %> guide to learn more.</p>

<%= h2_with_anchor "Configuration Wizard" %>
<p>Jumpstart Pro comes with a configuration wizard to help you enable and disable features quickly in development. For example, you can simply check a box or toggle a feature on/off, click Save &amp; Reload and your dependency will be installed and your Rails app restarted.</p>

<p>You can view the configuration wizard UI at <%= link_to nil, "/jumpstart", target: :_blank, class: "text-primary-500 underline" %> only in development</em>.</p>

